 1. Functional Requirements

Data Processing (Python)
  Load HR dataset using Pandas
  Clean data (remove duplicates, handle missing values)
  Transform data types (Age, Income, etc.)
  Create derived features:
  AgeGroup
  ExperienceLevel
  RiskLevel
  Export cleaned dataset as CSV for Power BI

Data Visualization (Power BI)
  Import cleaned dataset
  Build interactive dashboards
  Create KPIs using DAX
  Design charts for analysis:
    Bar chart
    Line chart
    Pie/Donut chart
    Scatter plot

Business Analysis
  Workforce distribution analysis
  Attrition pattern identification
  Employee risk analysis
  Satisfaction and performance evaluation

2. Non-Functional Requirements

  Dashboard should be interactive and responsive
  Data should load efficiently in Power BI
  Visuals should be clear and readable
  Clean and structured report output
  Easy navigation between dashboards

3. Software Requirements

  Python (3.x)
  Libraries:
    Pandas
    NumPy
    Matplotlib / Seaborn (optional)
    Power BI Desktop
    Microsoft Excel (optional for data viewing)

4. Hardware Requirements

  Processor: Intel i3 or above
  RAM: Minimum 4 GB (8 GB recommended)
  Storage: At least 500 MB free space
  Display: 1366×768 or higher resolution

5. Dataset Requirements

  IBM HR Attrition Dataset (100K records version or standard version)
  Must include:
    Employee details
    Attrition status
    Department
    Salary
    Job role
    Experience data

6. Tools & Technologies

   Python (Data preprocessing)
   Power BI (Dashboard creation)
   DAX (Calculations)
   CSV format (Data transfer between tools)

7. Output Requirements

  Clean dataset file (CSV)
  Power BI dashboard file (.pbix)
  Visual dashboards:
  Executive Overview
  Workforce Analysis
  Attrition Analysis
  Employee Health Dashboard
